# **Business Process Maps (Diagrams)**

Project: InstaCom (Web \+ Extension)  
Version: 3.0  
Format: Mermaid JS

## **1\. Extension "Auto-Launch" & Send Logic**

This flow ensures the "Receiver" is always active before a "Send" action can complete.

flowchart TD  
    Start((Click Ext Icon)) \--\> CheckTab{Web App Open?}  
      
    CheckTab \-- No \--\> Launch\[Open Web App (Pinned Tab)\]  
    Launch \--\> WaitForLoad\[Wait for 'Ready' Signal\]  
    WaitForLoad \--\> RenderGrid  
      
    CheckTab \-- Yes \--\> RenderGrid\[Render Tile Grid\]  
      
    RenderGrid \--\> UserAction{User Interaction}  
      
    UserAction \-- Hold Tile \--\> StartRec\[Start Mic Capture\]  
    StartRec \--\> DurationCheck{Duration \< 3min?}  
      
    DurationCheck \-- Yes \--\> Stream\[Stream to Server\]  
    DurationCheck \-- No \--\> ForceStop\[Auto-Stop Recording\]  
      
    Stream \--\> Release{Release Mouse?}  
    Release \-- Yes \--\> ValidateTime{Duration \> 300ms?}  
      
    ValidateTime \-- Yes \--\> Upload\[Finalize Upload\]  
    ValidateTime \-- No \--\> Discard\[Discard (Spam Protection)\]

## **2\. Server Routing & Echo Cancellation**

Visualizing how the server filters the sender and manages history.

graph LR  
    Sender\[User A (Ext)\] \--\>|Stream \+ SourceID| Server\[Node.js Server\]  
      
    subgraph Server Logic  
        Server \--\> CheckFilter{Filter SourceID}  
        CheckFilter \--\>|Exclude User A| BroadcastList  
          
        BroadcastList \--\>|Target: User B| B\_Status{User B Status?}  
        BroadcastList \--\>|Target: User C| C\_Status{User C Status?}  
    end  
      
    B\_Status \-- Active \--\> StreamB\[Stream to User B WebApp\]  
    B\_Status \-- AFK \--\> NotifyB\[Notify User B\]  
      
    C\_Status \-- DND \--\> HistoryOnly\[Save to History Only\]  
      
    StreamB \--\> JitterB\[User B Jitter Buffer\]  
    JitterB \--\> SpeakerB\[User B Speakers\]  
      
    Server \--\>|Save Blob| DB\[(Database)\]  
    DB \-.-\>|Audit Log| AdminConsole  
![][image2]

## **3\. Idle Detection Flow**

How the system handles "False Active" users.

stateDiagram-v2  
    \[\*\] \--\> Active  
    Active \--\> IdleTimer: No Mouse Move  
      
    state IdleTimer {  
        \[\*\] \--\> Counting  
        Counting \--\> Warning: 10 Minutes Elapsed  
        Warning \--\> AFK: 60s No Response  
        Warning \--\> Active: User Clicks Toast  
    }  
      
    AFK \--\> Active: User Manually Toggles Status
